Useful man pages recommended by /usr/games/fortune freebsd-tips

man boot0cfg  # repair damage to MBR caused by other OSes

man firewall  # advice on building a FreeBSD firewall
man hier      # the way FreeBSD systems are laid out

man intro     # 1:General 2:System calls 3:C libs 4:Device drivers 
              # 5:File formats 6:Games 7:Misc 8 Sysadmin, 9 Kernel

man ports     # installing FreeBSD ports
man security  # advice on securing FreeBSD system
man tuning    # advice on performance tuning a FreeBSD system

# man -k stat|grep "stat([18]" |grep -ve "built-in"

btsockstat(1)            - show Bluetooth sockets information
ctlstat(8)               - CAM Target Layer statistics utility
fstat(1)                 - identify active files
gstat(8)                 - print statistics about GEOM disks
ifmcstat(8)              - dump multicast group management statistics per interface
iostat(8)                - report I/O statistics
ipfstat(8)               - reports on packet filter statistics and filter list
kldstat(8)               - display status of dynamic kernel linker
ministat(1)              - statistics utility
netstat(1)               - show network status
nfsstat(1)               - display NFS statistics
pmcstat(8)               - performance measurement with performance monitoring hardware
procstat(1)              - get detailed process information
pstat(8), swapinfo(8)    - display system data structures
sockstat(1)              - list open sockets
stat(1), readlink(1)     - display file status
systat(1)                - display system statistics
vmstat(8)                - report virtual memory statistics
